Notable engagements in this box include: Duke University Race and Representation
              Conference, 1999; New York University Slave Routes: The Long Memory Symposium, 1999;
              Trip to Brazil, 1999; Stanford University Conference on Race, 1999.

Notable engagements in this box include: U.S. Department of State trip to South
              Africa, 2001; Library of Congress John W. Kluge Fellow, 2001-2003; Trip to Mali, 2002;
              The Citadel Conference on the Civil Rights Movement in South Carolina, 2003;
              University of Chicago Symposium to Honor John Hope Franklin, 2003.

Includes a folder of notes on her son John's birth and first year of life, 1952;
                work for charities such as the Chicago Child Care Society and the Illinois Children
                and Family Services; materials regarding her membership and work for the Links,
                Inc., a women's organization dedicated to supporting African American causes;
                several personal notebooks; and other materials.

Includes materials from Franklin's visits, including drafts of his lectures and other
              teaching materials; membership directories; reports and publications about ASPEC;
              logistical and administrative information from ASPEC visits.
